# Keep Documentation Current

After making significant changes (new features, completed build steps, new track results, schema changes), update the relevant documentation before finishing:

## Files to update

- **`trading_system_brief.md`** — The project's living reference. Update the V2 Build Sequence checkmarks (§5.9), track results (§5.10), and V3 prerequisites (§6.3) when tracks complete or new capabilities are added.
- **`RESEARCH_CONTEXT.md`** — Agent briefing document. Update the V2 Multi-Track Results table, per-track fitness numbers, and Status/Next Steps section when track runs finish or strategies improve.

## When to update

- A research track completes its iteration budget
- A new best fitness is achieved on any track
- A new data pipeline, track, or infrastructure feature is added
- Build sequence steps are completed

## What to update

- Mark completed build steps with ✅ and add result summaries
- Update fitness numbers, per-window breakdowns, and comparison tables
- Add new files/directories to the RESEARCH_CONTEXT files table
- Update V3 prerequisite status
